Recycled Packaging Materials Market Analysis
The U.S. Environmental Protection Agency's report that plastic and packaging waste account for nearly one-third of total annual trash highlights a significant market opportunity and a pressing challenge for the recycled packaging industry. This substantial proportion of waste underscores the urgent need for sustainable packaging solutions and drives the growing demand for recycled packaging materials. Innovations in recycling processes and the development of new types of recycled materials enhance the quality and availability of recycled packaging. These technological improvements enable companies to offer high-performance recycled packaging solutions, thus expanding market opportunities and meeting the increasing demand for sustainable packaging options.
Recycled Packaging Materials Market Size
Global recycled packaging materials market size was valued at USD 46.31 billion in 2023 and is projected to reach USD 70 billion by 2031, with a CAGR of 5.30% during the forecast period of 2024 to 2031. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include in-depth expert analysis, geographically represented company-wise production and capacity, network layouts of distributors and partners, detailed and updated price trend analysis and deficit analysis of supply chain and demand.
